The paper deals with signal processing methods for mitigating the effect of read-channel degradation in Flash devices. This involves channel estimation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a framework for on-line model-based channel estimation, which involves modeling and system identification (cs.AR). The paper also discusses numerical algorithms for channel estimation, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY) and engineering and technology (cs.ET). Finally, the paper uses statistical methods for binning channel measurements, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
